{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"738b545b-386b-4012-9cd4-474ce28c173c","content":"Here are the five things to fix for .NET 10:\n\n**1. InlineArray + explicit StructLayout → `TypeLoadException`**\n.NET 10 enforces that `[InlineArray]` types may not have `[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Explicit)]`. Remove the `StructLayout` attribute — the runtime controls the layout automatically.\n\n**2. `DriveInfo.DriveFormat` string changes on Linux**\n.NET 10 may return different filesystem type strings on Linux. Replace hardcoded string comparisons with case-insensitive checks and test on your target distro, as raw OS values are now returned.\n\n**3. NU1510 — pruned package references**\n.NET 10 SDK enables dependency pruning by default. To resolve warnings, either add explicit `<PackageReference>` entries for packages you directly use, or opt out:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <RestoreEnablePackagePruning>false</RestoreEnablePackagePruning>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Transitive NuGet audit now on by default**\n.NET 10 audits **transitive** dependencies for vulnerabilities (previously only direct). Update vulnerable transitive packages, or to revert to old behavior:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <NuGetAuditMode>direct</NuGetAuditMode>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nUpdating the packages is strongly recommended over suppressing.\n\n**5. `FilePatternMatch.Stem` is no longer nullable**\n`Stem` now returns `string.Empty` instead of `null`. Change:\n```csharp\n// Before\nif (match.Stem is null) ...\n\n// After\nif (string.IsNullOrEmpty(match.Stem)) ...\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"78dd8a97-6793-4acf-8471-aabb28be4d77","outputTokens":420,"requestId":"A440:1521A3:6BBFBAC:7441B51:6A03D1B4"},"id":"9a9f82e5-a99d-4d38-9911-b16996232bcc","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:19:57.247Z","parentId":"0aaa9048-9a88-46cd-a9fa-7b9dae1d94cb"}
